The Ontario government debt is the amount of money the Government of Ontario borrowed from the general public, institutional investors and from public-sector bodies. As of September 30, 2013 the Ontario government's total debt stood at CDN$288.10 billion. The interest on the debt was CDN$10.3 billion for the 2012-2013 Ontario budget at an effective interest rate of 4%. It represented 8.4% of the total budgetary expenses and is the fastest-rising cost for the Ontario government. The Debt-to-GDP ratio in 2015 was 39.4%, the highest in Ontario's history.
